<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-CosbyDonation     12-18 0198</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Cosby Donation,0204</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bill Cosby Donates $1.5 Million to Two Schools</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The president of Bethune-Cookman
College returned Saturday from a trip to New York with a $700,000
donation from entertainer Bill Cosby.
   Oswald Bronson received the check Friday at Cosby's home. Cosby
also gave $800,000 to Meharry Medical College in Nashville, Tenn.,
Bronson said.
   Cosby, one of the richest men in show business, has donated
millions of dollars over the years to traditionally black colleges,
including $20 million given to Atlanta's Spelman College last month.
   Bronson said Cosby wants the donation to Bethune-Cookman
earmarked for scholarships in natural and physical sciences.
   ``He was very interested in the strength of our science and
mathematics departments,'' Bronson said.
   Ernest Cook Sr., vice president for physical affairs, said the
money will be used to fund about 10 full four-year scholarships each
year.
   Bronson solicitated the donation when he met Cosby at a dinner
party two months ago. The college president said he was so
persistent that Cosby later joked he expected to find Bronson hiding
in his salad.
   Faculty members were stunned by news of the donation. Bronson
said Cosby had sworn him to secrecy.
</TEXT>
