<HEAD>Greece Recovers From Snow Storms</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Emergency crews worked Sunday to clear one
foot of snow from the streets of cities and villages in northern
Greece.
   The airport in the city of Salonica remained closed for the third
straight day as frigid temperatures and fierce winds kept the runway
at Mikra International Airport iced over, an airport official said.
   Storms that began Thursday dumped one foot of snow on Salonica.
   More than 150 remote mountain villages in northern Greece
remained snowed in, police said. Bulldozers and snow plows were
working round-the-clock to clear roads leading to the villages,
police said.
   Gale force winds tearing across the Ionian and Aegean seas also
kept ships tied up in most of the country's harbors.
   Olympic Airways, the national carrier, said more than five
domestic flights to Aegean islands were canceled Sunday because of
the fierce winds.
