<2ND_LINE>AM-Hotel Fire,0119</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Dead, More Than a Dozen Unaccounted For</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SOUTH BEND, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire swept through a downtown
residential hotel Sunday morning , killing at least one person,
authorities said. Sixteen people were unaccounted for.
   The fire in the four-story Morningside Hotel apparently began on
the third floor and quickly spread. One wall collapsed. The hotel
has 105 rooms, housing transients and some long-term residents, and
was built in 1924.
   About 100 evacuees were moved to a nearby church. Robert Ziker,
the hotel's owner, said resident Julius Wood died in his
fourth-floor apartment.
   Of the residents who were unaccounted for, authorities said it
was possible they were not home at the time.
