<HEAD>Angry Customer Kills Barber Over Haircut</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man angry about the haircut he received returned
to the barbershop with a gun and killed the barber, police said.
   Robert Willis, owner of Barber Bob's Barber Shop in east Denver,
was shot about five times Saturday by a man whose hair he had cut
earlier in the day, shop customers said.
   One customer, who asked not to be identified, said Willis seemed
upset while he was cutting the suspect's hair and that the two
argued about the haircut after Willis finished.
   After the man left, Willis told his daughter and others that he
thought the man probably was high on crack and he feared that he
might return.
   Willis was on the telephone talking to police dispatchers when
the man returned with a semi-automatic handgun and shot him.
   ``It appears to have been a dispute over a haircut,'' said police
Sgt. Daniel Yount, who said the dispatchers heard the shots over the
telephone. Willis was dead when officers arrived.
   Witnesses said the suspect, last seen running from the shop, had
an almost clean-shaven head and a 3-inch, crescent-shaped scar on
the back of his head.
