<HEAD>Belgian Priest Shot, Another Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman shot and wounded a Belgian
missionary who was about to celebrate Mass in a northern town, the
head of the priest's congregation said Sunday.
   Rev. Francis Jevaert also said another Belgian priest has been
missing since last month in the northern Cordillera mountains.
   Jevaert said Rev. Mike Haelterman was shot on Friday in Tabuk,
about 200 miles north of Manila, just before the scheduled morning
Mass.
   The assailant apparently escaped and Haelterman, parish priest of
the Bolanao district in Tabuk, was hospitalized and released,
Jevaert said.
   He said no motive has been established for the shooting, but
added that local radio stations had accused Haelterman of aiding
communist New People's Army guerrillas who are active in the area.
   ``For me, that is only hearsay,'' Jevaert said. ``I don't know if
that is the reason'' for the shooting, he added.
   The Rev. Leo van Winkel, parish priest of the nearby town of
Lubuagan, 25 miles southwest of Tabuk, was reported missing while
visiting several mountain villages in his parish, Jevaert said.
   He said parishioners last saw Van Winkel on Nov. 22, but did not
report him missing until Dec. 8, when the Belgian priest failed to
show up for a religious feast in the village of Tinglayan.
</TEXT>
