<HEAD>Two Arrests Made In Slaying of Teen In Crowded Shopping Mall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police on Sunday arrested two men in a gang
shooting at a crowded shopping mall that left a teen-age bystander
dead.
   Roger Leon White, 22, of Sepulveda and William Stalling, 18, of
Pacoima, were booked for investigation of murder and held without
bail in the fatal shooting Friday of Sergio Alpuche, 16, of Van
Nuys, said Detective Mel Arnold.
