<HEAD>With AM-Soviet-Quake, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II blessed nativity scene
figures presented by children Sunday and urged prayers for Armenian
children who will be homeless at Christmas because of the
devastating quake in the Soviet republic.
   The head of the Roman Catholic church made the appeal during the
traditional blessing service in St. Peter's Square. Roman children
