and into those of all children of the world, remembering in a
special way the children who lost their houses in these recent days
because of the disastrous calamities that struck their homeland,''
the pontiff said.
   Officials say about 500,000 people were left homeless in the Dec.
7 quake that killed an estimated 55,000 people and injured thousands.
